DPRK's Holidays Marked in Nepal and Laos 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 1 (KCNA) -- Round-table talks took place in Kathmandu and a meeting, a photo exhibition and a film show at the Laos-Korea Youth Friendship Centre on Mar. 20 and 25 on the occasions of the Day of the Sun and the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at the venues of the functions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and photos showing their immortal exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 C. P. Mainali, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Nepal Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist), said at the round-table talks that the progressive humankind significantly commemorates the 95th birth anniversary of Kim Il Sung as his idea, exploits and virtue are very great. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are working hard to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, he noted, adding: The world revolutionary people draw great confidence and courage from their vigorous struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After watching the Korean film "The Korean People's Army, Steel-like Ranks", the vice-secretary of the Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Youth Union stated that the KPA would win only victory in the future, too, thanks to the original Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Friendship Meeting Held with Chinese School Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 1 (KCNA) -- A friendship meeting with the delegation of Jilin Yuwen Middle School of China took place at Changdok School on Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were members of the delegation led by Director Han Fei and Minister-Councilor Guan Huabing and staff members of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Director of Changdok School Kang Jun Ho, teachers and students of the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants first placed a floral basket before the statue of President Kim Il Sung at the school before paying high tribute to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went round educational facilities of the school and the exhibition of achievements made by the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting to be followed by students' art performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants talked to one another about the need to boost the relations between the two schools associated with the revolutionary history of Kim Il Sung, deepening friendship.

War Drills in S. Korea under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 1 (KCNA) -- The south Korean Federation of University Student Councils reportedly made public a statement entitled "The U.S. forces should immediately stop the anti-north war exercises going against the February 13 agreement and threatening peace of the Korean Peninsula and go out of south Korea" on Mar. 29. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said the south Korean authorities should clearly understand that the RSOI and Foal Eagle joint military exercises are a traitorous action defaming the June 15 joint declaration and laying a stumbling block in the way of improving the inter-Korean relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the U.S. to retract the hostile policy towards the DPRK, stop the war exercises at once and withdraw its troops, source of threat to peace on the Korean Peninsula, from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, members of civic and public organizations of south Korea, including the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the People's Solidarity, the Reunification Solidarity and the Preparatory Committee for the Progressive Solidarity, jointly called a press conference in denunciation of the combined landing drill staged as part of the aggressive RSOI and Foal Eagle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release, read out at the conference, charged that the drill on the Manripho coast in Thaean County, South Chungchong Province is the most offensive one of the joint military exercises as it is aimed at "infiltrating into the west coast of the north and occupying Pyongyang" under the "OPLAN-5027".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The large-scale attack exercises for invasion of the DPRK were launched at a time when undertakings were going on to implement the agreement reached at the six-way talks. This is an act of hindering the developments toward peace on the Korean Peninsula and it casts doubt about the truth of dialogue much touted by the U.S. and south Korean authorities, the press release stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Religionists under the Religious Human Rights Center of south Korea held a prayer meeting and made public a statement saying that to stage war drills in this land is the evil deed.

Kim Il Sung's Feats for National Reunification Hailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 1 (KCNA) -- One of the most important exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung while leading the cause of national reunification is that he set forth one-Korea policy and invariably maintained it despite grim environment, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The one-Korea policy is precisely that of national independence to achieve the complete independence and sovereignty of the country and the nation, and it is a genuine patriotic policy for the dynamic development of a reunified country and the prosperity of the whole nation, the article says, referring to the immortal leadership exploits the President performed by arousing all the Koreans to the struggle for its implementation.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was none other than the President who made it sure that a historic joint conference of representatives of the political parties and social organizations in the north and the south of Korea was convened after the liberation of the country and nationwide struggle was waged to foil the moves of the sycophantic traitors to keep Korea permanently divided. It was also the President who waged the steady struggle to foil the separatists' moves to make "two Koreas".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the 1970s the first high-ranking political meeting was held between the north and the south and the historic July 4 joint statement was adopted. In the 1980s multi-faceted dialogues and negotiations were made between the north and the south, and an inter-Korean agreement and a joint declaration on denuclearization were adopted in the 1990s. All these achievements were unthinkable apart from the energetic leadership of Kim Il Sung who had wisely led the cause of the country's reunification under the uplifted banner of one-Korea policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three principles for national reunification--independence, peaceful reunification and the great nation unity--agreed on and declared by the north and the south, the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo, the ten-point program for the great unity of the entire nation and all other policies and proposals made by the Workers' Party of Korea for national reunification are consistent with the spirit of national independence and one-Korea policy reflecting noble patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was thanks to the President's noble idea of great national unity and his energetic leadership that a great progress had been made in the struggle to organizationally rally the Koreans from all walks of life in the north and the south and abroad under the banner of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The June 15 era of reunification in Korea and miraculous achievements made in the movement for its reunification under the banner of "By our nation itself" are unthinkable without the one-Korea policy advanced and consistently maintained by the President.

Glorifying Kim Il Sung's Feats for Building Rich and Powerful Country Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 1 (KCNA) -- It is necessary to intensify the struggle to firmly defend and exalt the exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung to build a rich and powerful country and further glorify our homeland as an invincible power demonstrating its dignity to the world and a paradise for the people, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's history of building a rich and powerful country is an immortal history of the peerlessly great man who had illumined the way to be followed by the country and the people with his clairvoyant foresight, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As they were guided by the idea, theory and policy of Juche the President clarified with his clairvoyant foresight, the army and people of the DPRK could victoriously advance the socialist revolution along the untrodden path and work the epoch-making miracle of building a socialist industrial state in just 14 years from scratch. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President had devoted all his efforts to the prosperity of the country and the happiness of the people, giving ceaseless on-site guidance till the last moments of his great life. His wise guidance resulted in emergence of the invincible military power, the single-minded unity and solid foundation of the self-supporting economy and the most advantageous socialist system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people heroically and successfully concluded the "Arduous March", the forced march and built powerful war deterrence guaranteeing the prosperity for all the generations to come. These historic victory and national auspicious event would have been unthinkable without the feats performed by the President in building a rich and powerful country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His exploits are now successfully being carried forward under the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Considering the President's lifetime intention as an absolute yardstick and giving priority to the work for glorifying his leadership exploits, Kim Jong Il has frequently visited those units honored with the President's on-site guidance while making an endless journey of inspection to frontline areas and guidance to different economic units. Such noble traits of his are the supreme representation of the revolutionary moral obligation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the "Arduous March" in the grim 1990s, Kim Jong Il firmly defended our idea, principle and revolutionary mode, the revolutionary heritages left by the President, and made a long journey for the Songun revolutionary leadership to defend the destiny of the country and the nation entrusted by the President. This revolutionary history of his will remain long in the history of the country.

U.S. Denounced for Burdening S. Korea with Cost for Transfer of U.S. Military Base 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 1 (KCNA) -- The United States and the south Korean authorities recently made a final agreement to finish the construction of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek by 2011 and burden south Korea with about 5.6 billion U.S. dollars out of 10 billion needed for the transfer of the U.S. military base in Ryongsan, Seoul, and the U.S. second division and the construction of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard, a spokesman for the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland (DFRF) issued a statement on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said: The U.S. seeks to keep its forces' presence in south Korea under the pretexts of "transfer of military base" and "relocation", instead of withdrawing its forces. The recent decision to burden south Korea with huge cost for them is an intolerable insult and a mockery of the south Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DFRF Central Committee vehemently denounces in the name of the entire nation the recent final agreement as an unpardonable crime as it wantonly ignored the independent desire of the south Korean people and infringed upon the dignity of the Korean nation, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It held that the people from all walks of life in south Korea should hold higher the slogan for the withdrawal of the U.S. forces and, for the present, turn out in the struggle against the humiliating agreement on share of the cost.

Day of Sun to Be Commemorated in Italy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- An Italian preparatory committee was inaugurated in Rome on March 23 to commemorate the Day of the Sun, the birthday of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Miriam Pellegrini Ferri, chairman of the Italian Committee for the Study of Songun Idea for Independence and Sovereignty, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee at its inaugural ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee decided to introduce the immortal exploits of Kim Il Sung and organize a seminar on the Juche idea and the Songun idea, a lecture meeting, a photo exhibition and other colorful events on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.

Actions against FTA Staged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- An all-people candlelight event in protest against the negotiations for signing the south Korea-U.S. FTA was reportedly held in the Seoul City Hall plaza on Mar. 28 under the sponsorship of the Headquarters of the All-People Movement for Checking the south Korea-U.S. FTA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the event denounced the U.S. and south Korean authorities for pushing ahead with the negotiations at a final phase despite the unanimous opposition of the people from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They declared that the candlelight lit by the people in demand of the stop to the negotiations will flare up in this land to give momentum to the struggle against the U.S. subjugation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting for opposing the negotiations for FTA and protecting the screen quota was held in front of the Posin Temple in Jongro, Seoul, under the sponsorship of the Moviemen's Measure Committee for Checking the Cultural Aggression and Protecting the Screen Quota of south Korea on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the Emergency Measure Committee of Agriculture, Stock-breeding and Fisheries Opposing the Signing of FTA, too, called a press conference in Seoul to bitterly condemn the acts of treachery of the south Korean authorities.

Japan Urged to Apologize for Abduction and Forcible Drafting of Koreans
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries are becoming evermore mean in their moves to cover up and play down the abduction and forcible drafting of Koreans committed by Japan in the past, loudly vociferating about an "abduction issue". The Japanese Ministry of Public Management, Home Affairs, Post and Telecommunications recently instructed NHK to continue handling the "abduction issue" as a major item in 2007, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday carries a signed article in this regard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should have knelt down and apologized to the Koreans for the abduction and forcible drafting of a great number of Koreans in the past, instead of denying the issue of "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army and raising a hue and cry over the already settled "abduction issue", if they had had sound thinking power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arrogant Japan, however, is impudent enough to insist on the "abduction issue" in a bid to mock the Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is national chauvinism and the idea of regarding the Koreans with contempt that prompt the Japanese reactionaries to deny the abduction and forcible drafting of Koreans including the crimes related to the sexual slavery committed by the Japanese imperialists in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The persistent distortion of history by the reactionary ruling circles of Japan is not attributable to simple individual feelings or insufficient understanding of history. It is guided by the idea of staging a comeback to Korea to put it under their control. Herein lie the danger and gravity of Japan's denial of its past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is foolish for the Japanese reactionaries to try to evade the responsibility for Japan's hideous war crimes by hyping the "abduction issue".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan can neither shake off the ill fame of an enemy state nor evade the world's accusing finger if it persists in its wrong attitude toward the past history.

Elimination of Anti-Reunification Conservatives Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- In order to implement the tasks of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity it is necessary to wage a dynamic struggle for eliminating the pro-U.S. reactionary conservative forces in south Korea including the Grand National Party standing in the way of the progress of the society and the reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the intrinsic demand of the national reunification movement to fight against the anti-reunification conservative forces, the article notes, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The national reunification movement is accompanied by a fierce struggle against the anti-reunification conservative forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The pro-U.S. conservative forces in south Korea are a main stumbling block lying in the way of implementing the above-said tasks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are becoming more desperate in their moves to hinder the development of the inter-Korean relations based on the idea of attaching importance to the nation and the national reunification movement, crying out for "cooperation" with the U.S., in disregard of the unanimous will and desire of the fellow countrymen to achieve the national reunification through the great unity of the whole nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There occur in south Korea more often than not such abnormal cases in which the June 15 joint declaration is debased as a "national disgrace" and those who contributed to the reunification and patriotism stand trial at "courts" to be punished. All this is attributable to the moves of the anti-reunification conservative forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality urgently requires the south Korean people to frustrate the plot of the pro-U.S. flunkeyist traitors including the GNP to return to power in a bid to bring again a nightmare of the fascist rule and drive the nation to a miserable end and throw overboard them to the last man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Given that the conservative organizations attempt to close their ranks organizationally in a bid to satisfy their greed for power with the "presidential elections" approaching, it is realistic and essential for all the progressive pro-reform and pro-reunification forces from all walks of life in south Korea to go united to prevail over them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unity is the key to all the victories. It is the truth taught by history that unity means victory and division means defeat.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Famous Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Saturday dedicates a signed article to the 25th anniversary of the publication of the famous work "On the Juche Idea" authored by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work reflects the unshakable faith and will of Kim Jong Il to accomplish the revolutionary cause started by President Kim Il Sung under the uplifted banner of the Juche idea, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il advanced the Songun political mode based on the Juche idea to meet the needs of the times and the developing revolution and has led the Korean people in their cause of socialism to a shining victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wise leadership provided by him for the victory of the socialist cause of Juche lies in that he clearly indicated the way for the times and revolution to follow through his energetic ideological and theoretical activities and steadily intensified the socialist education as required by the developing reality, thereby helping all the servicepersons and people emerge strong in idea and faith. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His wise leadership also lies in that he has ideologically motivated all the servicepersons and people to usher in the bright dawn of a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun idea serves as great revolutionary guidelines based on the Juche idea in the present times and an invincible banner for the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has emerged the strongest in the national history spanning 5,000 years and is making a leaping advance towards the eminence of a great prosperous powerful nation by dint of single-minded unity based on the revolutionary soldier spirit. This reality goes to clearly prove that the Songun idea serves as an invincible weapon for highly exalting the dignity and spirit of socialist Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has energetically led the struggle to bring about a heyday of a prosperous country, holding fast to the ideological work despite unprecedented ordeals and adversity in recent years. It is Kim Jong Il who has wisely led the officials to energetically enlist the revolutionary enthusiasm and creative ingenuity of the masses so that they may conduct the ideological campaign in a more dynamic and offensive way in the bold fighting spirit, neither wavering nor hesitating in face of any adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Immensely rosy future is now in store for Songun Korea as he is victoriously steering Korean-style socialism of Juche with his great idea and energetic leadership.

Juche Idea, Almighty Precious Sword for Socialist Cause
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- Twenty-five years have passed since Kim Jong Il made public his work "On the Juche Idea" on March 31, Juche 71 (1982). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work is a library and an encyclopedia on the Juche idea which comprehends and systematizes the Juche idea in a comprehensive way and develops it in depth as a new ideological and theoretical wealth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, in the work, expounds the principles and contents of the Juche idea and glaringly proves that it is the great guiding idea indicating the way for accomplishing the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last years, the validity, truth and vitality of the Juche idea have been confirmed as the almighty precious sword to carry the socialist cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many changes took place in the world political composition and socio- class structure in the last ten years of the 20th century and the Korean revolution had to go through the most arduous trial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At that time, Kim Jong Il took the Songun idea based on the Juche idea as the invariable guideline of the Korean revolution and applied it in all the fields of the revolution and construction to the letter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He laid down the Songun revolutionary theories such as the principle of putting the army ahead of the working class and the idea on the motive force in the revolution and thus gave most perfect answers to the theoretical and practical questions raised in the accomplishment of the socialist cause at present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular, he has directed primary attention to training the army and people of Korea as those strong in ideology and faith under the banner of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has made a long Songun journey without interruption to bring up the whole army as a rank of pure ideology and vanguard in defending the leader with its lives and conducted energetic activities for making the whole society replete with the revolutionary soldier spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this course, the ideological and moral qualities of the army and people of Korea have reached a new higher stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By dint of the ideological and moral power of the army and people who firmly believe only in Kim Jong Il and hold aloft his ideas and leadership with the will to share the fate with him, Korea could victoriously carry out the "Arduous March" and the forced march and usher in the dawn of the great, prosperous and powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will, in the future, too, achieve only victory in the revolution and construction under the uplifted banner of the Juche idea, almighty precious sword for the accomplishment of the socialist cause.

More than 160 Cases of Aerial Espionage against DPRK in March
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialist aggressor forces committed more than 110 cases of aerial espionage and the south Korean forces at least 50 cases against the DPRK in March, according to a military source. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Two U-2s of the U.S. forces based in south Korea made shuttle flights all day long on March 28 and 29 each to spy on the depth of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On March 21 overseas-based RC-135 of the U.S. forces was busy with aerial observation and photographing of all areas of the DPRK. This reconnaissance plane perpetrated espionage on March 5 and 8, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On March 28 and 30 Japan-based E-3 spied on areas of the DPRK while commanding the flying corps involved in the RSOI and Foal Eagle joint military exercises. On March 14 and 16 EP-3 was busy spying on areas along the west and east coasts of the DPRK and its frontline area. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the south Korean forces mobilized three or four RC-800 and RF-4C everyday to observe and photograph the frontline and central region of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These acts of aerial espionage perpetrated by the U.S. imperialist aggressor forces and the south Korean forces are a grave military provocation to the DPRK, an infringement upon its sovereignty.

S. Korean Authorities Urged to Retract Action Taken to Disconnect Internet Sites
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 31 (KCNA) -- The recent action taken by the south Korean authorities to disconnect Internet sites was a fascist action against democracy and human rights as it was aimed to blindfold the south Koreans and stop their ears and deprive them of even their right to enjoy the high civilization in the IT era and an act of treachery running counter to the basic spirit of the June 15 joint declaration. They should, therefore, retract the action at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A spokesman of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland demanded this in a statement Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the Defense Security Command of the south Korean army recently announced that it detected more than 30 "pro-north Internet sites" and disconnected them through the ministry of Information and Tele-Communications, etc., the statement went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities termed the DPRK's Internet homepages including "By our nation itself" and homepages of the organizations for the reunification movement in south Korea "undesirable or pro-north sites" and have so far prevented south Koreans from directly connecting them or making a free use of them. They are even harshly suppressing those who posted articles supporting the Songun politics on Internet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is something shameful for the nation that Koreans are barred from getting in touch with each other over Internet at present when news and information are exchanged among countries through Internet irrespective of distance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fact that even the above-said command was involved in the operation to detect "pro-north Internet sites" reminds one of what the military fascists committed in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities would be well advised to remember that such action will only invite criticism and derision of the public at home and abroad.

Meeting for Koreans' Human Rights Held in Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, March 30 (KNS-KCNA) -- A meeting of women for Japan-resident Koreans' human rights and Japan-Korea peace was held in Tokyo on March 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were Japanese women engaged in the movement for solidarity with the Korean people and the chairwoman of the Central Standing Committee of the Korean Democratic Women's Union in Japan and other Korean women in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Addressing the meeting, Sumiko Shimizu, representative of the Japanese Women's Society for Solidarity with the Korean Women, said that the Japanese government authorities are pursuing the one-sided policy of sanctions against the DPRK for their sinister political purpose and the atmosphere of rash suppression of Koreans in Japan is prevailing over Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then a lecture was given on such subjects as "On the situation of human rights abuses against the Koreans in Japan".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A video CD on the Japanese reactionaries' suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan and Koreans in Japan was displayed before a resolution was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution strongly demanded that the government of Japan apologize and compensate for its past aggression and colonial rule over Korea on the basis of the Japan-DPRK Pyongyang Declaration and thus dissolve mutual distrust, settle the pending problems through dialogue and establish the Japan-DPRK diplomatic ties.

Comite Preparatorio de Italia para el Dia del Sol
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 31 de marzo (ATCC) -- Quedo constituido el dia 23 en Roma el Comite Preparatorio de Italia para el Dia del Sol (15 de abril, cumpleanos del Presidente Kim Il Sung). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Como su presidente fue electo el titular del Comite Italiano de Estudio de la Idea del Songun (priorizacion militar) para la Independencia y la Soberania, Miriam Pellegrini Ferri. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La entidad naciente decidio propagar las inmortales hazanas del Presidente y organizar seminario sobre la idea Juche y la del Songun, conferencia, fotoexhibicion y otras diversas actividades.

Rodong Sinmun aboga por liquidar las fuerzas anti-reunificacion
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 31 de marzo (ATCC) -- Para materializar las tres tareas: la preponderancia de la nacion, la defensa de la paz y el logro de la unidad, debemos desplegar con vigor la lucha por eliminar el "Gran Partido Nacional" y otras fuerzas conservadoras reaccionarias y pronorteamericanas del Sur de Corea, que impiden el progreso social y el avance del movimiento por la reunificacion de la patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Senala asi el diario Rodong Sinmun en un articulo individual publicado este sabado y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La lucha contra las fuerzas conservadoras anti-reunificacion es la demanda intrinseca del movimiento por la reunificacion de la patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Este movimiento implica la encarnizada batalla contra las fuerzas conservadoras anti-reunificacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las fuerzas conservadoras proyanquis del Sur de Corea devienen un obstaculo principal en la materializacion de las tres tareas arriba mencionadas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El "GPN" y otras fuerzas conservadoras proyanquis desprecian la unanime voluntad de la nacion de lograr la reintegracion territorial del pais con la gran unidad nacional, y, al clamar por la "cooperacion" pronorteamericana, obstaculizan obstinadamente el movimiento por la reunificacion de la patria y el desarrollo de las relaciones Norte-Sur a base de la preponderancia de la nacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Debido a las maniobras de dichas fuerzas, en el Sur de Corea la Declaracion Conjunta del 15 de Junio se tilda de "verguenza nacional", las personas honestas que contribuyeron a la causa patriotica por la reunificacion se citan a comparecer al "tribunal" para recibir castigo y ocurren con frecuencia semejantes casos anormales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La realidad requiere imperiosamente frustrar el complot de usurpacion del "Poder" del "GPN" y otras fuerzas serviles a las grandes potencias y eliminarlos completamente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Dado que las entidades conservadoras pretenden una confabulacion organizada para la toma del Poder en visperas de las "elecciones presidenciales", todas las fuerzas surcoreanas aspirantes a la reforma progresista y a la reunificacion deben unirse compactamente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La llave de todas las victorias es la unidad. Vence al unirse y se derrota al desunirse, lo cual es una verdad de la historia.
